Chic and urban decor. Excellent but friendly service. Cuisine fitting for the big city. Our favorite place in Ithaca.

Great overall experience service/setting. NOLA shrimp and meatballs were good appetizers and my short rib was perfectly cooked. Mom found the bbq burger sauce a bit heavy, but my sister loved it! Cocktails good as well!

Great food, good drinks at a relaxed pace. We enjoyed our experience here.
Great atmosphere and great food!
Very good food and atmosphere. Severely underrated on Google — should definitely be closer to 5 stars.

Great food and service.  A great variety on the menu and the food, including the desserts were great.

Amazing food, incredible service, would absolutely come back. We ordered the lobster ravioli which had massive pieces of lobster in it and the buffalo cauliflower which was so delicious. The wait staff was very kind and helpful. One of the best restaurants in Ithaca and all local/farm to table!

Great experience. Locally and ethically sourced ingredients. Creative specials. Seasonal menu. Generous portions. Good ambiance and friendly staff. Definitely recommend!
Great place - love the school/student part, great cocktails - closes early sometimes without notice.

Have been here a few times and have always been happy with the food and service.  Appetizers in particular are interesting and delicious.  Atmosphere is also really quite nice.
